children.subject: Just as a warning, CS184 apparently has very high workload (close to 162 level) depending on your professor. I haven't taken it personally, but that's what a lot of people have told me.

history.content:
I would recommend EECS 126 (Yes, it's EECS now), Math 110, or CS 189 as a third.

CS 189 should only be taken if you already have a strong Linear Algebra + Probability background if you're taking it with 2 other technicals.

If you don't have a strong Linear Algebra or Probability background, I would recommend EECS 126 or Math 110. 126 and 110 open a lot of doors for future courses, research, and related special topics courses.

I would also recommend reconsider taking a third technical if you can avoid it, and instead swap 186 with 126/110.

_________________________________________________________________________________________

Definitely disagree^ 126 and 189 are both very difficult classes and if you have not taken many upper div technical courses at a time before before 170 + 189/126 would be asking a lot. 188/168/161 sound like they would be better.

children.subject: 184 got cancelled apparently, by the way

I agree with the second student response a lot more than the first. CS 100 is also a really good class to take with those two, especially because there's some overlap between it and 186 that you'll appreciate. It's not a super high workload class either (7 homeworks, 8-12 hours each on average) spread out over the semester and it's a slightly less difficult 189 that gets coverage on a lot of 189 topics before you jump straight into the fire. 161 is also good but projects are long and and decently difficult. I would say it was significantly more work than 100

history.content: Hi I am wondering what three CS upper divs you'd recommend taking concurrently. Currently I'm enrolled in 170 and 186. I've never taken three technicals in one semester, but I've found two to be manageable. What third would you recommend? I was thinking 188 if it opened, if it doesn't maybe 184? Thanks.
